# npm configuration — committed to the repo (no secrets here).
#
# What this file does:
#   Line 1 (registry mapping): tells npm to fetch any package whose name starts
#     with `@mcp-rune/` from GitHub Packages instead of the default
#     registry.npmjs.org. Without this, `npm install @mcp-rune/mcp-rune`
#     returns 404.
#   Line 2 (auth token reference): tells npm where to find the bearer token for
#     npm.pkg.github.com. The `${GH_PACKAGES_READ_TOKEN}` syntax is npm's env
#     var interpolation — npm reads the value from the shell at install time,
#     so the secret never lives in this file or in git history.
#
# Where the env var comes from:
#   • Local dev:  mise (sops-encrypted ~/.config/mise/secrets.env.json)
#   • CI:         GitHub Actions repo secret `GH_PACKAGES_READ_TOKEN`
#                 (.github/workflows/test.yml, security.yml pass it as env)
#   • Docker:     Kamal builder.secrets in config/deploy.yml mounts it as a
#                 BuildKit secret (--mount=type=secret,id=GH_PACKAGES_READ_TOKEN)
#
# First-time setup (PAT + mise + sops): docs/guides/github-packages-setup.md
# npm config reference: https://docs.npmjs.com/cli/v11/configuring-npm/npmrc

@mcp-rune:registry=https://npm.pkg.github.com
//npm.pkg.github.com/:_authToken=${GH_PACKAGES_READ_TOKEN}
